All I have to say is that if this is true (I'm keeping my ranger in JP for a while, not taking him to SF to investigate this) it has got to be the worst GM decision I've read about.<br>
<br>
Personally, though this might seem rather harsh, if I was the GM who made that call I'd have handled it differently.  Total guildwar, last guild with any members standing in the zone wins an immediate Rage spawn, no buff time or anything, DT anyone from those 5 guilds who pops in after the guildwar is started, with a GM rez after Rage is either killed, or kills those still alive to fight him.  Rage DT's if the winning guild cannot kill him. <br>
<br>
